# Confidential VM kernel config overrides.
#
# This fragment inverts certain hardening choices for steep's confidential VM
# threat model where the initrd is measured (RTMR[2] for TDX, launch digest
# for SNP) and therefore part of the trust boundary rather than an attack
# surface.

# Re-enable ACPI table upgrade. In the standard Linux threat model this is
# risky because the initrd is untrusted. In steep's confidential VM model
# the initrd is measured into RTMR[2] (TDX) and bundled into the IGVM launch
# digest (SNP), so a tampered initrd fails attestation. We use this feature
# to ship a trusted DSDT that overrides VMM-supplied AML — defeats the
# BadAML attack vector.
CONFIG_ACPI_TABLE_UPGRADE=y
